commitResults.messageBody:
Following the AB3 guide, users currently have an 'address' field which
stores their home location

This makes sense for an AddressBook, but as iVolunteer primarly
manages volunteers and events, there is no need to store the address of
each volunteer

Let's remove the address field of volunteers

In the next few commits, let's change the 'tag' field of each volunteer
to 'skills'

commitResults.messageTitle: Change vfind to search by partial names

commitResults.messageBody:
The current vfind command allows users to find a volunteer by name.
However, it does not allow users to find by partial name, nor does it
allow to find by volunteer's skills

This needs to be changed because finding by partial name will add a
layer of convenience to users who may have to otherwise type out a long
name, while finding volunteers by skill is an essential feature of
iVolunteer

Lets revamp the vfind command to enable the aforementioned features.
Also fixed the broken test cases due to refactoring and made a couple
new ones.

commitResults.messageBody:
Originally, in the base app, there was only 1 list that displays
Volunteer. This adds an extra column to the main window of the GUI such
that it can display events. This involves the addition of a few classes,
namely EventCard, EventListPanel.

Refactored some other volunteer GUI elements as well.

Changed the title of the GUI app to iVolunteer.

Also fixed a bug where events don't load from EventStorage due to the
DateTime format being different from LocalDateTime that is saved into
EventStorage. This is fixed through the DateTime::toString() method
to save the DateTime in the format as specified in the ecreate command.
